          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"loss\">Loss</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">For each <code>(problem, clean_trace, corrupted_trace)</code> triple in a batch:</span>\n<ol>\n<li><code>e_clean      = energy_model(problem, clean_trace)</code>     \u2014 online encodes problem, <strong>JEPA target</strong> encodes the clean trace.</li>\n<li><code>e_corrupted  = energy_model(problem, corrupted_trace)</code> \u2014 online encodes problem, <strong>JEPA target</strong> encodes the corrupted trace.</li>\n<li><code>loss = mean( relu(margin + e_clean \u2212 e_corrupted) )</code></li>\n</ol>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Gradients flow into the <strong>online encoder</strong> and <strong>fusion head</strong> only; the JEPA\ntarget encoder is updated solely by the EMA step at the end of each iteration.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
